cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "tool-crowding: A pre-registered benchmark for discrimination interference in multi-MCP code retrieval"
message: "If you use this benchmark, methodology, or data, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Devanshu
    family-names: Chicholikar
    email: chicholkar.d@northeastern.edu
    affiliation: Northeastern University
    orcid: ""
repository-code: "https://github.com/DevanshuNEU/tool-crowding"
url: "https://github.com/DevanshuNEU/tool-crowding"
abstract: >-
  tool-crowding measures discrimination interference among
  concurrently-installed Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers on a held-constant
  code-retrieval task. The benchmark sweeps N (number of installed servers)
  as a continuous independent variable, isolates the discrimination effect
  from prompt-length capacity via a padded-N=1 control adapted from Chroma's
  text-retrieval methodology, and publishes per-server Marginal Performance
  Delta as a diagnostic. Pre-registered with four locked scenario abstracts
  before pilot data; all results ship with paired-bootstrap confidence
  intervals and a 7-artifact content-addressed run identity chain.
